Hi Raffaela,

From my Assessment I am satisfied that there is no loss of structural integ=
rity to the downstairs of your property.

David from Asset Restore feels the same which is why he and his team are ha=
ppy to get in to clean the property.

Once all remaining debris is removed from site we will look to get 2-3 quot=
es from separate Tower preferred builders.
While these builders are on site, they will do a thorough inspection and if=
 for some reason they feel that a structural engineer is required, then at =
that stage we would engage one.

I have since authorised for Asset Restore to commence works plus have asked=
 for an electrician and gas contractor to attend.
I=E2=80=99ve also emailed David Tallot your questions and he has sent the b=
elow response.

To answer the questions bellow,


  *   I will engage an electrician to do a make safe before we start our wo=
rk =E2=80=93 we can do our work from generators if needed.
  *   It=E2=80=99s up to you on the engineer, I didn=E2=80=99t see anything=
 that would make me think there is a risk of collapse, while working onsite=
 when linings come down if anything is noted I can get a builder to put pro=
ps in, and we can then let an engineer inspect the site.
  *   I Have allowed to remove the heavily smoke damaged asbestos as per ph=
oto which is less than 10m2. =E2=80=93 the only risk is that I can see is i=
f you need to remove the entire quantity to match a product that would be i=
nstalled next to it this would increase quantity being removed to greater t=
han 10m2 requiring a clearance. =E2=80=93 considering its not burnt we can =
leave it in situ until the repair plan is made ?
  *   I didn=E2=80=99t see the gas unit onsite; I can arrange plumber gas f=
itter to arrange make safe.
  *   If there is mould carrying out the strip out will better expose where=
 it is and allow the building to dry so if needed further remediation can b=
e done before repairs.

thanks

David Tallott
Manager
[cid:image001.jpg@01DBE6A7.72EAF7D0]




Kind Regards,

[cid:image002.png@01DBE6A7.72EAF7D0]
Chris Cornwall
Structural Assessor
021 734 732
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
