Raffaella del Prete &lt;raffaellanz@icloud.com&gt;
<br>
<b>Sent:</b> Thursday, 26 June 2025 11:21 am<br>
<b>To:</b> Chris Cornwall &lt;Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz&gt;<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Tower Claim - C90306048<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Chris, Thank you again for sending through t=
he Asset Restore scope of works and for all your efforts in helping move my=
 claim forward. I=E2=80=99ve reviewed the document
 and truly appreciate the work being done to progress the reinstatement for=
 23<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p>Hi Chris,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thank you again for sending through the A=
sset Restore scope of works and for all your efforts in helping move my cla=
im forward. I=E2=80=99ve reviewed the document and truly appreciate the wor=
k being done to progress the reinstatement
 for 23 Mays Street, Devonport.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">As we discussed over the phone, before we=
 proceed, I=E2=80=99d like to raise a few questions=E2=80=94I hope you don=
=E2=80=99t mind me checking in this way. My goal is to ensure everything is=
 addressed safely and in the right order:<o:p></o:p></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
A qualified master electrician has assessed the house and advised it=E2=80=
=99s not electrically safe, especially with the new switchboard and wiring.=
 Has a formal licensed electrical inspection been scheduled to confirm safe=
ty before re-entry?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-mar=
gin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
As we spoke, there are structural beam damages, and the significant smoke t=
raveling through floors, walls, and out all sides of the roof suggests exte=
nsive heat stress. The wetness and dampness from firefighters might have wo=
rsened these structural issues.
 Would it be prudent to have a structural engineer assess the building befo=
re any removal or cleaning begins?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" s=
tyle=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 leve=
l1 lfo1">
Regarding asbestos, the quote mentions less than 10m=C2=B2 of ACM material =
for removal, but the attached photo shows the damaged lower deck section is=
 closely connected to the main deck, possibly indicating more extensive inv=
olvement. Would a full asbestos inspection
 be a wise step to rule out broader risks?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoN=
ormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list=
:l0 level1 lfo1">
The gas unit, exposed to heat and smoke, concerns me. Has a technician been=
 arranged to inspect the system and fittings for safety?<o:p></o:p></li><li=
 class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
Lastly, the firefighting water use and a leak shutdown suggest potential mo=
isture or mould damage in hidden areas. Should we arrange an assessment for=
 water or mould damage before reinstatement?<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">On a related note, I was wondering about =
the work sequence. The quote focuses on cleaning for reinstatement, but mig=
ht it be better to start with removal and cleaning just for assessment? Thi=
s could allow engineers and specialists
 to evaluate hidden damage (e.g., behind linings) and ensure a safe restora=
tion plan=E2=80=94does that sound reasonable?<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99d also kindly ask if you could =
share plans to help me stay informed and involved, and if we should regular=
ly catch up=E2=80=94perhaps weekly via email or a quick chat? That would be=
 really helpful for me.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I am happy to see we are moving forward a=
nd very keen as the accommodation allowance is limited, and would love to r=
eturn home and resume normal life as soon as it=E2=80=99s safe. These quest=
ions come from a place of care and collaboration,
 and I really appreciate your time in considering them.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thanks again for your support. I look for=
ward to your thoughts.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Kind regards,<br>
Raffaella del Prete<o:p></o:p></p>
